spanGrp.span: A mister was playing, and there was something that chased him,
Pekaga jinõ-ra-mĩ (_) rö ele jirö kate të í töjiá
so he quickly entered where the tiger was;
je nẽ jẽk pakká plaja nãmã kate jãrga
He could not touch anything because he dropped everything he grabbed.
ñerö ka ĩã jirö kar ta (m) porke jirö klabe guge-gẽ-wã-ite jãr-gẽ-te í yiga
So, he opened something and so the other one frightened him.
Ñerö mẽnẽbi jirö köyajá-wã-ite ñerö jeska e-gla kate të mẽlechá-wã
He did not know it was there;
and then the dog bit him in the foot.
(_) ñerö (m) chichi demĩũ-te í kwá í klöga
There came a girl she fain/she fell on her head because she did not know what to do.
Ñerö pebusi demĩũ-te pebusi desma/ í mẽnẽũ-mĩ tsaguga porke ka í juenẽ ta jirö we-gẽ-ite rö inga
The man asked her to open the door;
Ñerö pekaga të shá ĩã-nã jũkö yeu-mĩ-te (_)
Pekaga të í pakká jũkö yeu-mĩ ĩã
The tiger stood up but did not do any harm to him;
Nãmã jẽk kagá ka wã jirö wanẽ ĩã
The tiger stood up but did not do any harm to him;
nãmã rö julbö e-gla nãmã ka të jirö wẽ kuna
The girl told him to get out quickly because the tiger could devour him.
Pebusi të shá ĩã-nã í jẽk yusá betebe porke nãmã í kete-mĩ-wã
So the man pretended to caress the tiger, but the tiger frightened him.
Ñerö í kayuwö-gẽ-nã í mãũ-te nãmã pakse-gẽ ñerö (m) nãmã të í mẽlechá-wã
So he came out and did not see anything.
Ñerö í desãũ ka wã í sunẽ ta
The tiger remained inside and the girl closed the door.
ñerö nãmã nãmã jatanã'tanã kötiá-wã pem/ pebusi të
and and gave his hand to the girl.’
Ñerö pemi/ pebusi ĩã í jula mõ-gẽ
